Perhaps what is needed is an engine for things like collision and movement that makes designing object behaviors almost as easy as it is in WarioWare DIY. Nintendo has got it to the point where AI is just Action Instructions. Sure, it would be limited, probably to single-screen games, but then at least people would be able to make their own NES games with less need for obsessive dedication.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue May 18, 2010 7:53 am</p><hr />
